race.comment: BEAUTY EDGE (7) made it two wins on the trot when he led throughout in a gutsy performance over 1200m at Cowra last start. Jumps from a BM58 to a BM74 but drops 6.5kgs to compensate. Coming back in trip is no bother so expect him to prove tough to run down again. INAZUMA BOY (6) has performed well without threatening in his three runs since a long break. Responded under pressure to be beaten less than three lengths over this trip in town last time out. Nicely drawn and finds the right race to make his mark. CANAMBLE (9) won a Class 3 at Scone two back then had a let-up before a modest effort here most recently. Suited by a slightly longer trip today and from a favourable draw should get every chance. BRUTAL LOVE (1) returns from a brief spell. Good fresh performer who is yet to miss the top three in four visits here. Ticks the right boxes. BRIEF STATEMENT (8) has been in the money at five of six runs over this course and distance. Right in the mix with the light weight.
